definitions: (of a structure) having fallen down or given way

examples.text: an abandoned building with a collapsed roof

definitions: (of a lung or blood vessel) flat and empty with the walls fallen inward

examples.text: he was admitted to hospital with a collapsed lung

definitions: (of a person) having fallen down and become unconscious

examples.text: police officers rushed to the aid of the collapsed woman

shortDefinitions: having fallen down and become unconscious

examples.text: compensation for workers in collapsed pension plans
